.SH "NAME"
CheckDigits::MBase_003 \- compute check digits for SICI (Serial Item
and Contribution Identifier)
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&  use Algorithm::CheckDigits;
\&
\&  $sici = CheckDigits(\*(Aqsici\*(Aq);
\&
\&  if ($sici\->is_valid(\*(Aq0784\-8679(20040308)6:<138>2.0.TX;2\-H\*(Aq)) {
\&        # do something
\&  }
\&
\&  $cn = $sici\->complete(\*(Aq0784\-8679(20040308)6:<138>2.0.TX;2\-\*(Aq);
\&  # $cn = \*(Aq0784\-8679(20040308)6:<138>2.0.TX;2\-H\*(Aq
\&
\&  $cd = $sici\->checkdigit(\*(Aq0784\-8679(20040308)6:<138>2.0.TX;2\-H\*(Aq);
\&  # $cd = \*(AqH\*(Aq
\&
\&  $bn = $sici\->basenumber(\*(Aq0784\-8679(20040308)6:<138>2.0.TX;2\-H\*(Aq);
\&  # $bn = \*(Aq0784\-8679(20040308)6:<138>2.0.TX;2\-\*(Aq;
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
.SS "\s-1ALGORITHM\s0"
.IX Subsection "ALGORITHM"
.IP "0" 4
In the string describing the number all letters (A\-Z) are replaced
with numbers 10\-35 accordingly. All other non-numbers are replaced by
36.
.IP "1" 4
.IX Item "1"
Beginning right the numbers at all odd positions are added.
.IP "2" 4
.IX Item "2"
The sum from step 1 is multiplied by 3.
.IP "3" 4
.IX Item "3"
Beginning right the numbers at all even positions are added.
.IP "4" 4
.IX Item "4"
The sums from step 2 and 3 are added.
.IP "5" 4
.IX Item "5"
The sum from step 4 is taken modulo 37.
.IP "6" 4
.IX Item "6"
The checksum is 37 minus the sum from step 5 where numbers from 10 to
35 are represented by 'A' to 'Z' accordingly and 36 is represented by
\&'#'.
.SS "\s-1METHODS\s0"
.IX Subsection "METHODS"
.IP "is_valid($number)" 4
.IX Item "is_valid($number)"
Returns true only if the last letter is a valid check letter according
to the algorithm given above.
.Sp
Returns false otherwise,
.IP "complete($number)" 4
.IX Item "complete($number)"
The check letter for \f(CW$number\fR is computed and appended the
end of \f(CW$number\fR.
.Sp
Returns the complete number with check letter or ''.
.IP "basenumber($number)" 4
.IX Item "basenumber($number)"
Returns the basenumber of \f(CW$number\fR if \f(CW$number\fR has a valid check
digit.
.Sp
Return '' otherwise.
.IP "checkdigit($number)" 4
.IX Item "checkdigit($number)"
Returns the check letter of \f(CW$number\fR if \f(CW$number\fR has valid check
digits.
.Sp
Return '' otherwise.
